        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_kalm" xml:lang="os">
                <form type="lemma"><orth>kalm</orth></form>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>змея</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>snake</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>червь</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>worm</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>kalm jæ særæj mardæ ū</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>змею убивают в голову</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the snake is killed in the head</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>III
                            210</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>kalmaw myn mæ rīw sūʒgæ bawwyldta mast</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>как змея, источило мне грудь жгучее горе</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>burning grief ate into my chest like a snake</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>18</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Общеиндоевропейское слово, означавшее ‘червь’, др.иран.
                    %i*kṛmi-%i, и.е. %i*k˳rmi-%i. Значение ‘червь’ не чуждо и осетинскому; об этом
                    говорит аблаутный вариант этого же слова <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kælm"/>
                    ‘червивый’ (%iys-kælm īs%i ‘очервивел’), %ikælmxærd%i ‘изъеденный червями’; ср.
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wallon"/>, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_zulk’"/> ‘червь’. Переход %ir%i → %il%i под влиянием %ii%i
                    (ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_talm"/>). Др.иран. %iṛ%i → ос. %ial%i (←
                    %iаr%i), как %iard%i ← %iṛta-%i, %imard%i ← %imṛta-%i и др. Ср. <mentioned
                        xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>kirm</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>karm</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="mzn"><lang/>
                        <w>karm</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="glk"><lang/>
                        <w>kalm</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ku"><lang/>
                        <w>kurm, kurum</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgh"><lang/>
                        <w>čīrəm, čirm, čerm</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="srh"><lang/>
                        <w>čerm</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="yah"><lang/>
                        <w>karm</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"><lang/>
                        <w>kərm</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Зарубин._Мундж."/><biblScope>150</biblScope></bibl>),
                        <mentioned xml:lang="yai"><lang/>
                        <w>kirm</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>kyrm, qrm</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>kərəma-</w></mentioned> (?), <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>kṛmī-</w>
                        <gloss><q>червь</q></gloss></mentioned>; <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><lang/>
                        <w>kirmis</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ga"><lang/>
                        <w>cruim</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-tchr"><lang/>
                        <w>aca-karm</w>
                        <gloss><q>удав</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_ZDMG"/><biblScope>XCIV 142</biblScope></bibl>). —
                        <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/>
                        <w>чрьвь</w></mentioned> (<mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>червь</w></mentioned>) содержит, по-видимому, тот же корень, но с другим
                    формантом и относится к %i*kṛmi-%i, ос. %ikalm%i так же, как, скажем, лат.
                    %ipulvis%i к ос. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fælm"/>; ср. также <mentioned
                        xml:lang="orv"><lang/>
                        <w>чермень</w></mentioned> рядом с %iчьрьвень%i ‘красный цвет’.%n<bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 50, 66, 89,
                            111</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>36</biblScope></bibl>. —
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."
                            /><biblScope>46</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>51, 150</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">A common Indo-European word, which means ‘worm’, Old Iranian
                    %i*kṛmi-%i, Indo-European %i*k˳rmi-%i. In Ossetic the meaning ‘worm’ existed as
                    well; it is proved by the ablaut variant of this word <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_kælm"/> ‘wormy’ (%iys-kælm īs%i ‘become worm-eaten’),
                    %ikælmxærd%i ‘worm-eaten’; cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wallon"/>, <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_zulk’"/> ‘worm’. The transition %ir%i → %il%i is
                    under the influence of %ii%i (cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_talm"/>). Old
                    Iranian %iṛ%i → Ossetic %ial%i (← %iаr%i), as %iard%i ← %iṛta-%i, %imard%i ←
                    %imṛta-%i etc. Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>kirm</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>karm</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="mzn"><lang/>
                        <w>karm</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="glk"><lang/>
                        <w>kalm</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ku"><lang/>
                        <w>kurm, kurum</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgh"><lang/>
                        <w>čīrəm, čirm, čerm</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="srh"><lang/>
                        <w>čerm</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="yah"><lang/>
                        <w>karm</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"><lang/>
                        <w>kərm</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Зарубин._Мундж."/><biblScope>150</biblScope></bibl>),
                        <mentioned xml:lang="yai"><lang/>
                        <w>kirm</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>kyrm, qrm</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>kərəma-</w></mentioned> (?), <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>kṛmī-</w>
                        <gloss><q>worm</q></gloss></mentioned>; <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><lang/>
                        <w>kirmis</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ga"><lang/>
                        <w>cruim</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-tchr"><lang/>
                        <w>aca-karm</w>
                        <gloss><q>boa</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_ZDMG"/><biblScope>XCIV 142</biblScope></bibl>). —
                        <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/>
                        <w>чрьвь</w></mentioned> (<mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>червь</w></mentioned>) apparently contains the same root, but with a
                    different formant, it is related to %i*kṛmi-%i, Ossetic %ikalm%i the same way
                    as, say, Latin %ipulvis%i to Ossetic <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fælm"/>; cf.
                    also <mentioned xml:lang="orv"><lang/>
                        <w>чермень</w></mentioned> and %iчьрьвень%i ‘red colour’.%n<bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 50, 66, 89,
                            111</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>36</biblScope></bibl>. —
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."
                            /><biblScope>46</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>51, 150</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
